  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1964",
  "title": "Configure keeps values that no longer exist",
  "body": "**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\n- Pass { insideBoundingBox } to Configure\r\n- Remove it and pass only { aroundLatLng }\r\n- Configure is put into the url twice: \r\n\r\n```\r\n\"&configure[insideBoundingBox]=42.0095169,-114.131211,32.528832,-124.482003&configure[aroundLatLng]=33.7489954,-84.3879824\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expect if there's no props on configure, the values will be removed from the search state :) \r\n\r\n**What project are you opening an issue for?**\r\n- react-instantsearch\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n\r\n3.1.0",
